About Me

Driving Results Through Strategy & Execution

Combining analytical thinking with creative problem-solving to deliver measurable business impact

Professional Background

Based in Seattle, Washington, I am a marketing and operations professional with a proven track record of driving business growth through strategic initiatives. With a Bachelor's degree in Business Management & Communication from Western Governors University and recent certification in Strategic Thinking and Innovation, I bring a unique blend of academic knowledge and real-world experience to every project.

Core Philosophy

I believe in the power of data-informed decision-making combined with human-centered creativity. Whether I'm optimizing CRM systems at HubSpot, coordinating $15K nonprofit events, or leading international teams, my approach centers on strategic planning, meticulous execution, and continuous improvement. Every project is an opportunity to create meaningful impact and drive measurable results.

Unique Value Proposition

What sets me apart is my diverse experience across marketing, operations, and international leadership. From increasing social media engagement by 30% to reducing operational waste by 20%, I consistently deliver results that exceed expectations. My multilingual capabilities (English, French, Lingala) and cross-cultural experience enable me to connect with diverse audiences and lead teams that span geographical and cultural boundaries.
